funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to replace the HVAC system that will improve air quality and create energy efficiency for a not for profit organization that provides an essential service to children in the foster care system in Atlantic County and Cape May County.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to complete a feasibility study to create/develop a Wind Innovation and New Development Institute. The institute would consist of an advisory board that would serve as the states central location for research, development and knowledge-sharing related to the production, transmission and use of wind and other renewable energy solutions. They would also provide feedback on the workforce needs of the offshore wind industry.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: REAP-MANDATORY RENEW ENERGY SYST GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development Investment will be used to purchase and install a 66 kilowatts (kW) roof mounted solar array for Tuckahoe Turf Farms in Hammonton, Atlantic County, New Jersey. The farming operations include twelve hundred acres, all family owned for over 100 years, eight hundred are cultivated, primarily in sod. The remaining five hundred acres consist of permanently preserved watershed, wetlands, and service areas. Tuckahoe Turf Farms is one of the largest growers of sod in the Northeast and a leader in new and innovative varieties of sod and growth technology. This project, when completed, will generate 85,353 kilowatt hours (kWh) with an annual savings of $14,429.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: MAND.ENERGY EFFIC IMPROV GRANTS UNDER $20,000
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase and install a 150 HP Electric Irrigation Motor. The sod farm, which has over 800 acres, is replacing their diesel motor for an electric motor which is a cleaner energy source. This project, when completed, will generate 18,501 kilowatt hours of energy over a 248 hour period for a 78 percent savings.

funding_code: CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Construction (23)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase a boom lift with a 50 foot tow. The Public Works Department will be able to effectively perform maintenance on the borough streets after storms and major weather events. This new equipment will help maintain safety for the residents in this small rural community.

funding_code: ECONOMIC IMPACT INITIATIVE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
naics_description: OTHER FIRE/RESCUE & PUBLIC SAFETY RELATED SERVICES
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase a new 180 kilowatts generator for the City of Wildwoods Public Works Department. The Public Works Department does not currently have a backup generator, which leaves them vulnerable during times of flooding and power outages. The new generator will allow the Public Works Department to have access to alternative power if the facility loses power from the electrical grid during an emergency situation. Having a new generator will allow the Public Works Department to respond to emergency situations quickly and effectively.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase a new generator for the city of Wildwoods Water Utility Department located in the Park Avenue facility. funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) PRE-DEVELOPMENT GRANTS - WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used for predevelopment planning for Cape May Citys water treatment and desalination plant. The project entails completing a feasibility study, alternatives analysis, and conceptual design for the expansion of their existing plant. This upgrade expansion is needed to increase firm production capacity and address current and future water demands.

funding_code: RBCS DEVELOPMENT GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used for a feasibility and implementation study to provide broadband service to five rural municipalities within the County of Cumberland. The proposed project will not directly affect a specific business, but rather serve as an accelerator for communities in the five rural municipalities. The county is seeking quotations from qualified vendors to conduct a broadband feasibility study and develop a comprehensive economic and community telecommunications strategy. The ideal vendor will have excellent technical and analytic depth in broadband implementation and must be high-effective communicators, particularly in translating technical concepts to non-technical audiences. The vision of the County of Cumberland is to provide a broadband speed telecommunications infrastructure to the entirety of their community. Broadband is a critical service for a quality of life and economic development. Every home, business, non-profit organization, government entity, and education institute should have the opportunity to connect affordably, easily, and securely.

naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development Investment will be used to purchase and install a 12 kilowatts (kW) raised ground mounted solar array for Red Skye Farms in Cumberland County, New Jersey. Red Skye Farms is an agriculture producer and a rural small business on 44 acres. The new 2021 raised ground mounted solar structure will preserve the land under the photovoltaic panels for farm use and avoid shading from the adjacent barn. This project, when completed, will generate 16,000 kilowatt hours (kWh) with an annual savings of $4,192.

naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
naics_description: OTHER FIRE/RESCUE & PUBLIC SAFETY RELATED SERVICES
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase a new emergency rescue boat for the Downe Township Fire and Rescue Company (the Rescue Company). The new equipment includes a 20 foot aluminum Sonar Boat, a trailer, Garmin GPS package, and a station for sonar operations. The existing rescue boat is old and unreliable which makes it more difficult for the Rescue Company to perform sonar rescue operations. The new boat and equipment will substantially improve the Rescue Companys ability to complete water rescues in the nearby Delaware Bay and will significantly improve public safety.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to launch new distribution using online tools, markets, and methods. Shippetaukin, LLC doing business as Cherry Grove Farm, is a diversified livestock farm located near Princeton, New Jersey. The farm adds value to their raw materials through processing. This project will create two new full time jobs for the farm.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase new equipment for the Borough of Penns Groves Police Department and Fire Department. funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) ECWAG - APPROPRIATED $1,000,000 LIMIT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to make improvements to the water treatment plant by adding a granulated activated carbon (GAC) treatment system to remove per fluorinated compounds/contamination from the well water. The granulated activated carbon (GAC) system will consist of two carbon absorber vessels, associated piping, valves and activated carbon media. The system will be enclosed in a small, shed structure which is also proposed as part of the project. All other aspects of the existing treatment plant will remain in place and will not be modified. Since the emergency backup for the Borough in Bellmawr is now closed due to PNFA chemical infiltration and the 2 Brooklawn wells usage have been stopped with NJ DEP violations. The improvements will allow the plant to service 1955 rural residents and 80 commercial businesses with safe water meeting NJ DEP standards.

funding_code: RBCS DEVELOPMENT GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to improve the economic development and growth of downtown Wildwood by completing the engineering phase of the Cedar Ave Pedestrian Connector project. The project is designed to attract pedestrian traffic from the Wildwood Boardwalk down a welcoming corridor and into the Pacific Avenue Business District. The USDA participated in Phase I of this project, which was to complete initial design for this Connector. This Phase II project would see those designs engineered and developed into a completed set of plans and specifications, which would allow the Business Improvement District to move forward with procurement and construction of this project.

project_name: FY 22 W. Washington Water Main cost overun
funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to update a tuberculated water main system with a new eight-inch diameter cement lined ductile iron pipe water main along West Washington Street from Delaware Street to Penn Line Road. The proposed replacement will improve water circulation, chlorine residual, and fire flow availability. It will also reduce the potential for water main breaks, poor water pressure and water quality. The roadway will be restored with full width roadway reconstruction following installation of the new water mains.

funding_code: (WWA PROGRAM AREA) SOLID WASTE GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to build specialized artificial intelligence based virtual reality modeling for identifying threats to water resources in landfills exacerbated by climate change. This includes training and education to landfill operators, solid waste commission members, and residents of rural communities of Deerfield Township, Fairton, Cedarville, Seabrook Farms, and South Harrison in Gloucester County New Jersey.

funding_code: LAMP VALUE ADDED PRODUCER GRANT MANDATORY
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used by Global Agricultural Productions, LLC (GAP) to implement a direct-to-customer strategy and complete the expansion of its packing and shipping facilities in order to open the door to new markets such as restaurants and farmers markets, and ultimately including subscription plans. GAP is a fully sustainable grower, packer and shipper of organic blueberries known as FullBlues. FullBlues blueberries are among the largest and most superior tasting blueberries on the market. GAP have developed an innovative, proprietary technology to produce premium quality organic blueberries, tripling the per acre yield over conventional growing methods and reducing water usage by 50-70%, by relying on a precision irrigation system.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: DISCR RENEW ENERGY & EFFIC GRANTS UNDER $20,000
naics_industry_sector: Professional, Scientific, and Technical Services (54)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help Goodwink Farms purchase and install a 10 kW solar array. This project will replace 12,297 kWh (87.26%) per year. Goodwink Farms provides horse training and veterinary services and is owned by Margaret Sleeper.

funding_code: LAMP VALUE ADDED PRODUCER GRANT MANDATORY
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
naics_description: ADMINISTRATION OF HUMAN RESOURCE PROGRAMS (EXCEPT EDUCATION, PUBLIC HEALTH, AND VETERANS' AFFAIRS PROGRAMS)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to offset post-harvest labor, delivery labor and marketing costs associated with growing Gristmill Granges Community Supported Agriculture (CSA) membership by the 2023 season. With an anticipated expansion of 2000 new members, 14 fulltime positions will be open in the wash/pack barn for post-harvest handling of the raw commodity, along with 7 additional full-time drivers to help with the increase in demand. The CSA is the only sales/distribution method utilized on the farm, and its customers choose them due to its organic certification and accessibility. Gristmill Grange offers home delivery with an in-house team of drivers and fleet of vans ready to deliver within a 400-mile radius from its farm.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to expand locally grown produce sales to new and existing customers by pickup and truck delivery program. project_announced_description: The Rural Development investment will be used to help Salem residents that are utilizing small business incubator spaces receive the education to help them be more successful with their business. Each entrepreneur will have the opportunity to receive the education that will provide the technical assistance that will help their business thrive and increase the opportunity to maintain and sustain their business, so each entrepreneur can be more sustainable and be able to provide more for their families by providing a needed service to the community and potential low moderate income job growth.

funding_code: (COMB LOAN & GRANT) WASTE DISPOSAL ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to expand the sanitary sewer system conveyance capacity to service future commercial development in the Township of Carneys Point. A new sewer force main will be installed from the Carneys Point waste water treatment plant to the existing Game Creek pumping station. Another sewer force main will be extended from the Game Creek pump station to the Kelly Farm at the intersection of East Quillytown Road and Route 48. This second force main will provide for connection points and manholes adjacent to existing properties to be developed. AIR/vacuum relief valves will be installed along the length of the force mains at all local high and low points. The Game Creek pump station will also be upgraded as part of this project to handle the additional flows.

funding_code: CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
naics_description: OTHER FIRE/RESCUE & PUBLIC SAFETY RELATED SERVICES
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase upgraded emergency communication radios and a pickup truck for the fire department. Current radios are antiquated, and do not allow communication with departments on lower bands, or communication with other municipalities. The new radios will make operations easier for the fire department to communicate with the law enforcement department and to be ahead of the impending switch to 800 mandorty broadcast zone (MBZ) band for emergency services. The new vehicle will be used as a deputy chiefs command vehicle and a utility vehicle for water rescue calls and other natural disaster related emergencies.

funding_code: (COMB LOAN & GRANT) WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to add additional treatment facilities to the Rocky Hill water plant in order to remove contamination as mandated by the NJ Department of Environmental Protection with a new Granular Activated Carbon system. A back-up potable water well will be installed as part of this project to ensure adequate capacity is provided by the water system. The deteriorating water system on Crescent Avenue will be replaced with a new water main pipe, hydrants, and valves.

naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to create infrastructure to expand the sales and use of renewable fuels. Pinkavas Motor Company Inc is the owner of ten or fewer fueling stations. This project will replacetwodispensers and two storage tanks at one fueling station located in New Jersey. Stations locations impacted by this grant are: Springfield. This project projects to increase the amount of ethanol sold by 8,315 gallons per year. The purpose of this funding program is to assist owners of transportation fueling and fuel distribution facilities in activities designed to expand the sales and use of ethanol and biodiesel.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: The Rural Development investment will be used to grow and expand the Food Hub Pilot Project connecting rural farms in New Jersey with wholesale and retail customers in population-dense communities in New Jersey. The benefits of further developing the food hub are to 1) encourage an increase number of farm operations in New Jersey; 2) increase agricultural job opportunities, including but not limited to on-farm operations and retail/wholesale distribution of local food products; 3) increase the availability of healthy local food grown in New Jersey for the consumption of New Jersey residents; and 4) improve the environmental health of New Jersey s farmland by promoting growing practices that meet the National Organic Standards (recommended criteria to participate in the food hub).

program: Meat and Poultry Processing Expansion Program
funding_code: MEAT AND POULTRY PROCESSING GRANTS - ARPA
naics_industry_sector: Manufacturing (31-33)
project_announced_description: New Goffle Road Poultry is located in Wyckoff, NJ with the closest plant of similiar processing located in central Jersey. There are no facilities in New York or Connecticut that provide the kind of servicing and processing that Goffle Road Poultry provides. Goffle Road Poultry seeks to expand the existing USDA inspected processing facility and retail operation to be six times the size of the current facility with a separate retail store. The company will also create a satellite pickup and drop-off area for other farms within and tangential to New Jersey, which is currently unavailable and highly desired by producers. Expansion will allow the company to expand further into the organic marketplace by allowing for efficient seperation of organic vs. non-organic product. Halal market reach, a growing need in the area, will also be expanded including cut-up products and parts associated with halal markets.

funding_code: REAP IRA RES GRANT UNRESTRICTED (FY 22/23)
naics_industry_sector: Manufacturing (31-33)
naics_description: GASKET, PACKING, AND SEALING DEVICE MANUFACTURING
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase and install a 304.3 kilowatt (kW) fixed tilt, roof mounted direct current (DC) solar photovoltaic (PV) system. Nolato Jabar LLC is a U.S. manufacturer and development partner of EMI shielding, thermal interface materials, commercial silicone sealing and damping solutions. This project is expected to lower the companys energy usage by 32 percent per year.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: ENERGY EFFICIENT EQUIPMENT GUARANTEED LOANS
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
naics_description: OTHER FOOD CROPS GROWN UNDER COVER
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be to purchase and install energy efficient equipment to build-out and operate a vertically integrated controlled environment grow out facility for the Omakase and Koyo strawberries from Japan. The project will convert a vacant building in Phillipsburg, New Jersey, into a production facility to serve the east coast premiere strawberry market. The facility will include a high tech indoor vertical farming operation, harvesting facility, packaging facility and shipping and distribution facility that will create 45 new jobs for area residents and reduce operating costs by $150,000 annually. The project is groundbreaking for future agricultural production and efficiency.
